node.text:
It's time to be proud of 😁🏅Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory) 

📷 @meghancoyle

G L U T E S🔥 Share your posts with us and we will share them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory 

Amazing sequence of body weight exercises to train hamstrings and glutes muscles supporting on a sofa 🛋

Try doing 3 rounds of each exercise - videos are indicating how many reps per round🙌🏻
📽 @mariela.bravo.fit

On the right track ☺️ Apply to promote your content in our account, go to our link in bio: @RunningTerritory 

"Going to keep you updated soon about my back recovery, but we‘re on course. 👍🏻 It can be tricky sometimes but the longer I get to deal with that old back injury, the more experience I have and the better I (& with my team of therapists of course) am becoming in dealing with such issues.

Sorry that I‘m failing at responding to all your sweet comments/DMs atm… having 2-3 therapy sessions each day besides training takes up a lot of time and keeps me busy. But it’s worth it! I promise improvement and being more active here on IG again soon ✌🏻🙏🏻🙃"

📽 @tstroschneidertri

node.text:
by @mitchjackson 💪 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures.

There's something special about going for a run.

It clears the mind.

It removes the stress.

It makes me feel like a better human being.

Running allows me to be a better lawyer. It helps me be a better person.

How about you?

What do you enjoy most about running? Please share in the comments below.

Thanks!

@mitchjackson

EPIC Abs Work 🔥 Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory)

Bodyweight ONLY

SAVE + LIKE + SHARE + CRUSH IT 👊🏼

The weather had been getting warmer, so you know I’m excited about that. Soon soon, I’ll get able to get after some awesome outdoor workouts and bring them to you 🤗 Today I did this intense ab session. This is advanced and one needs to ensure that the bench is WELL counterbalanced - here I used the smith machine and loaded the bar with weights to hold the bench in place. Core should be kept tight and engaged at all times. Tailbone tucked slightly under so the lower back is protected. 🙏🏻
I also did a CrusHIIT (from my HIIT style workout series see my stories) 💚

Workout deets: 8-16 reps for 3-4 sets. On the hanging hollow body hold 15-20 secs (key to tuck pelvis under and hold core tight)
📽 @senada.greca

⁉️ Having trouble setting up your feet in the correct position for the Bulgarian Split Squat (Rear Foot Elevated Split Squat)?

😎 Don't worry! Here's a super simple tip you can start using today so that you never find yourself hopping around awkwardly and off balance again!
